text: "I Can't Quit You Baby" is a 1956 song by blues singer Otis Rush. It was the first recording for the Cobra Records company. It became a record chart hit as well as a blues standard. In 1969 British band Led Zeppelin for their debut studio album Led Zeppelin. ==References== Category:1956 songs Category:Led Zeppelin songs Category:Blues rock songs
title: I Can't Quit You Baby
